entry.title: OOBE: Separate out getDeviceId message handler from gaia_dialog
entry.content:
gaia_dialog.js is shared between the regular login screen and the

enrollment screen. The current message handler for "getDeviceId" message

handler lives in gaia_screen_handler.cc, and gets called even for the

enrollment screen.



This can be a bit counterintuitive. To make the message passing more

explicit - move the message registration for "getDeviceId" into

gaia_signin.js. This file is not shared with the enrollment screen

handler. Also, rename the message name in the lower level JS - C++

interface to "getDeviceIdForLogin" to avoid confusion.



Bug: b/309929814

entry.title: Remove DCHECK for checking shelf icon click behavior
entry.content:
Three DCHECK were added in crrev.com/c/4688956 as a temporary solution

to address naming confusions from code that goes back to 10 years ago.

As was discussed in b/315364997, the DCHECK failed to address a specific

case when the user first uses tab key to locate the icon, and then uses

the enter key to launch the app.



As not one but quite a few keyboard input combination can be used to

launch an icon on the shelf, such as first tab then enter, or with

ChromeVoX running first tab then space, a DCHECK that specifically

checks certain keycodes is not a viable option. This CL removes all

three DCHECK, while updating the documentation to try to create a most

comprehensive context on the origin of the confusing naming disparity

between key press and key release events.

TEST: CQ

entry.title: Fix MF Crash due to `consume_handle_` is invalid.
entry.content:
The root cause should be cauesd by `consumer_handle` is invalid and

continuously read the null buffer, and each null buffer will execute

callback whichin batch mode, which caused the crash.



This CL change the way to read buffer by mojo_decoder_buffer_reader_,

OnBufferReady() will call ReadDecoderBuffer() one time instead of using

for loop. If the callback OnBufferRead() get a valid buffer, then call

ReadDecoderBuffer() again to read next buffer. If meet one null buffer,

this indicates batch read operation should done(including

`consumer_handle` is null and normal situation).



CL did not result in power saving regression.

entry.title: Update TopAlignedImageView to never add letter/pillarbox
entry.content:
Prior to this CL, when a landscape image was displayed, its height

matched the view height, and its width was smaller than the view's

width, ending up with a pillarbox effect (vertical bands on each side of

the image).

With this CL, preparing the way for landscape grid cells, the view is

now favoring matching its width when the image is narrower than the

view, and its height, when the image is wider than the view. This means

that there is never letterbox or pillarbox, i.e. there is always some

clipping. When clipping the width, the image stays centered. When

clipping the height, as the class aludes, the top is preserved and the

bottom is clipped.



But there is an exception because a Tab Grid animation needs a wider

image to fit in width with the view‚Ä¶ So this CL gets a bit more compelx than desired.

Bug: 1508874



Original change's description:

> Update TopAlignedImageView to clip the bottom instead of pillarbox

>

> Prior to this CL, when a landscape image was displayed, its height

> matched the view height, and its width was smaller than the view's

> width, ending up with a pillarbox effect (vertical bands on each side of

> the image).

> With this CL, preparing the way for landscape grid cells, the image is

> now always matching the image width, even if that means clipping the

> bottom or adding an horizontal band at the bottom.

entry.title: [iOS] Ensures test fails gracefully if cookies are not available
entry.content:
When a test suite is executed, it should be able to run each tests,

even the tests that fails. This means that no test should cause the

program to halt, because of CHECK or of invalid memory.



Earl-grey tests do not stop when an assertion fails. This means that

we can not protect CHECK and memory using EG assertions. The test

will fail but the code should either ensure the run ends or allows the

test to go on as much as possible.



The method to retrieve cookies in earl-grey failed with a DCHECK after

an assertion. This CL ensures that the assertion is logged as failing,

but, instead of triggering a DCHECK, the method returns nil.



Since on objective-C any method can be call on nil, this will not

cause the test to crash later.

entry.title: WebNN: Fix UBSan failure for XNNPACK reshape to scalar test case
entry.content:
When XNNPACK backend reshapes to 0-D scalar where the new shape is

empty, there is an UndefinedBehaviorSanitizer (UBSan) failure, for

example [1]. The previous implementation uses a `WTF::Vector` to

represent the new shape. `WTF::Vector` doesn‚Äôt allocate a buffer for an

empty vector. That causes `new_shape.data()` to return nullptr which is

passed to XNNPACK and used as the source address for `memcpy`.



This CL fixes this issue by using a stack-allocated array to represent

the new shape instead. Its address would be valid even when the array is

empty.



[1]: https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/linux-ubsan-fyi-rel/1272/test-results?sortby=&groupby=&q=xnnpack

entry.title: [file manager] add fusebox-Downloads volume
entry.content:
This adds a fusebox version of the Downloads folder, when the existing

chrome://flags#fuse-box-debug is enabled. This flag is not intended for

end-users to opt into. It is for CrOS developers.



When debugging fusebox problems, using a fusebox-wrapped LOC (local)

volume is usually more predictable (fewer moving parts; no network

involved) than a fusebox-wrapped non-local volume. Examples of the
